♪ You build all the big guns ♪

989
00:46:39.762 --> 00:46:43.490
♪ You build the big planes ♪

990
00:46:44.663 --> 00:46:47.805
♪ And you build the big bombs ♪

991
00:46:50.324 --> 00:46:53.672
♪ You hide behind walls ♪

992
00:46:55.502 --> 00:46:58.677
♪ And you hide behind desks ♪

993
00:47:00.783 --> 00:47:03.061
♪ I just want you to know ♪

994
00:47:03.199 --> 00:47:06.271
♪ I can never done nothin'... ♪

995
00:47:09.965 --> 00:47:11.380
We gotta go.

996
00:47:11.518 --> 00:47:13.865
["Masters of War" by
The Staple Singers continues]

997
00:47:14.901 --> 00:47:19.215
♪ You play with my world.
mm. mm ♪

998
00:47:20.423 --> 00:47:22.770
♪ Like it's your little toy ♪

999
00:47:24.565 --> 00:47:25.566
Nah. we don't.

1000
00:47:25.704 --> 00:47:28.742
♪ You put a gun in my hand ♪

1001
00:47:28.880 --> 00:47:30.675
They're scared of us.

1002
00:47:30.813 --> 00:47:33.885
♪ And you hide from my eyes ♪

1003
00:47:36.163 --> 00:47:37.924
♪ Then you try
to run farther... ♪

1004
00:47:38.062 --> 00:47:40.374
KATHY:
<i>I think it terrified him.</i>

1005
00:47:43.481 --> 00:47:46.622
You know. that's a lot of power
for one guy to have.

1006
00:47:46.760 --> 00:47:48.727
You know.
to be in charge of alla that.

1007
00:47:48.866 --> 00:47:50.533
I mean. that can really mess
with your noodle.

1008
00:47:50.557 --> 00:47:53.215
- Cream?
- DANNY: No.

1009
00:47:59.531 --> 00:48:01.464
You know. Benny was bad off.

1010
00:48:04.329 --> 00:48:06.193
Now. I had him in a motel
for three weeks.

1011
00:48:06.331 --> 00:48:07.643
I mean. he couldn't walk.

1012
00:48:07.781 --> 00:48:09.852
so I got him a place
with no stairs.

1013
00:48:09.990 --> 00:48:12.199
[over TV]:
This is my husband. This is...

1014
00:48:13.097 --> 00:48:14.417
- MAN: Darrin.
- [canned laughter]

1015
00:48:14.546 --> 00:48:15.789
[both laughing]

1016
00:48:15.927 --> 00:48:17.008
DARRIN: Oh. we were
just having a drink.

1017
00:48:17.032 --> 00:48:18.619
Would you care for a cocktail?

1018
00:48:18.757 --> 00:48:20.735
- I'd like a very dry martini.
- [knocking at door]

1019
00:48:20.759 --> 00:48:22.658
Italian Vermouth. Spanish gin

1020
00:48:22.796 --> 00:48:24.522
- and a Greek olive?
- [canned laughter]

1021
00:48:24.660 --> 00:48:26.120
DARRIN: Well. I don't think
we have any of...

1022
00:48:26.144 --> 00:48:27.939
- [knocking at door]
- WOMAN: Don't bother.

1023
00:48:28.077 --> 00:48:29.492
I'll fix it myself.

1024
00:48:29.630 --> 00:48:31.322
[canned laughter]

1025
00:48:34.670 --> 00:48:35.670
[shuts off TV]

1026
00:48:39.709 --> 00:48:40.709
Hey. Kathy.

1027
00:48:40.779 --> 00:48:42.781
Come on in.

1028
00:48:43.955 --> 00:48:45.370
Hey. look at you.

1029
00:48:45.508 --> 00:48:46.889
All propped up.

1030
00:48:47.027 --> 00:48:48.166
Like the queen.

1031
00:48:48.304 --> 00:48:49.996
Who you callin' a queen?

1032
00:48:50.134 --> 00:48:52.895
[chuckles] Ah. you look good.
You're looking all right.

1033
00:48:53.033 --> 00:48:54.666
The guys thought
you might really be out of it.

1034
00:48:54.690 --> 00:48:56.934
He is out of it. He can't walk.

1035
00:48:57.624 --> 00:48:58.832
What'd the surgeon say?

1036
00:48:58.970 --> 00:49:01.662
They. uh. cut through a tendon.

1037
00:49:01.800 --> 00:49:02.974
JOHNNY:
Oh. Jesus.

1038
00:49:03.112 --> 00:49:04.355
KATHY:
We're outta ice.

1039
00:49:04.493 --> 00:49:05.597
JOHNNY:
Oh. yeah.

1040
00:49:05.735 --> 00:49:07.116
They tie it back together
or what?

1041
00:49:07.254 --> 00:49:08.611
- BENNY: Somethin' like that.
- JOHNNY: Mm-hmm.

1042
00:49:08.635 --> 00:49:10.982
- I'm gonna go get some ice.
- So. uh...

1043
00:49:11.120 --> 00:49:13.053
So. how long they keep you
in the hospital for?

1044
00:49:13.191 --> 00:49:15.642
- BENNY: Three or four days.
- JOHNNY: That's a long time.

1045
00:49:27.171 --> 00:49:29.173
[sighs]

1046
00:49:29.311 --> 00:49:31.244
JOHNNY: The guys would love
to see you out there.

1047
00:49:31.382 --> 00:49:32.970
It's gonna be a big one.
you know.

1048
00:49:33.108 --> 00:49:34.350
maybe the biggest one yet.

1049
00:49:34.488 --> 00:49:36.214
Biggest what?

1050
00:49:36.352 --> 00:49:37.743
Picnic. Johnny's sayin'
they're goin' all out

1051
00:49:37.767 --> 00:49:38.767
for the Dayton run.

1052
00:49:38.837 --> 00:49:40.701
Oh.

1053
00:49:40.839 --> 00:49:42.289
BENNY:
How long is that? Three weeks?

1054
00:49:42.427 --> 00:49:44.084
JOHNNY: Yeah.

1055
00:49:44.222 --> 00:49:45.579
BENNY: I mean. I'll still be
in the cast by then. but...

1056
00:49:45.603 --> 00:49:46.984
Cast?

1057
00:49:47.122 --> 00:49:48.616
Cast. nah.
You shift with your left foot.

1058
00:49:48.640 --> 00:49:49.997
You can always
use your front brake

1059
00:49:50.021 --> 00:49:52.092
if you can't put
no pressure on it.

1060
00:49:52.990 --> 00:49:54.370
I know the guys. they would...

1061
00:49:54.508 --> 00:49:56.717
[ice rattling loudly]

1062
00:50:02.516 --> 00:50:04.415
You want a drink Johnny?

1063
00:50:04.553 --> 00:50:06.037
I'm good.

1064
00:50:06.175 --> 00:50:08.212
The guys would love
to see ya out there.

1065
00:50:09.282 --> 00:50:11.008
You know.
they're real worried about ya.

1066
00:50:11.905 --> 00:50:14.632
- I'll be there.
- All right.

1067
00:50:16.323 --> 00:50:17.324
I'll get out of here.

1068
00:50:17.462 --> 00:50:19.740
I'll let you rest.

1069
00:50:19.878 --> 00:50:21.328
Okay.

1070
00:50:21.466 --> 00:50:23.296
Kathy.

1071
00:50:28.370 --> 00:50:29.923
[door closes]

1072
00:50:30.717 --> 00:50:32.443
[motorcycle engine starts]

1073
00:50:36.102 --> 00:50:37.562
I mean. you wouldn't
really try riding

1074
00:50:37.586 --> 00:50:39.357
- after three weeks. would ya?
- [lighter clicks]

1075
00:50:39.381 --> 00:50:41.531
The doctor said three to four
months with no weight on it.

1076
00:50:41.555 --> 00:50:42.555
I don't know.

1077
00:50:42.660 --> 00:50:44.593
Turn up the TV. will you?

1078
00:50:44.731 --> 00:50:46.457
[scoffs]

1079
00:50:47.251 --> 00:50:48.873
I don't want you ridin'.

1080
00:50:50.909 --> 00:50:53.429
Yeah. it scares me. especially
this soon after surgery.

1081
00:50:53.567 --> 00:50:55.362
I-I don't like it.

1082
00:50:57.088 --> 00:50:59.573
- You don't like it?
- I get worried.

1083
00:51:06.235 --> 00:51:07.892
I should just go.

1084
00:51:09.376 --> 00:51:10.895
I'm just gonna leave.

1085
00:51:11.033 --> 00:51:13.000
- What?
- No. it's better.

1086
00:51:13.139 --> 00:51:15.106
- You'd be better off.
- Stop. Stop it.

1087
00:51:15.244 --> 00:51:17.488
Not having to take care of me.

1088
00:51:17.626 --> 00:51:18.937
- Worry about me.
- No.

1089
00:51:19.076 --> 00:51:20.905
No.

1090
00:51:21.906 --> 00:51:24.529
When I heal up. I'll leave.

1091
00:51:28.775 --> 00:51:30.121
[sighs softly]

1092
00:51:55.974 --> 00:51:58.011
I don't want you to go.

1093
00:52:08.435 --> 00:52:10.817
[pensive music plays]

1094
00:52:19.481 --> 00:52:22.829
I'm going off the freeway
into this. uh. ice plant.

1095
00:52:22.967 --> 00:52:24.393
I don't know if you know
what ice plant is.

1096
00:52:24.417 --> 00:52:25.797
If you're ever in California.

1097
00:52:25.935 --> 00:52:27.258
stop and look if you want.
but. like...

1098
00:52:27.282 --> 00:52:28.386
Hey. Kathy.

1099
00:52:28.524 --> 00:52:30.388
KATHY:
Hey. Brucie. How's Gail?

1100
00:52:30.526 --> 00:52:32.908
She's good. She's. uh. got
a job doin' nails in Oak Park.

1101
00:52:33.046 --> 00:52:34.185
I'll go see her.

1102
00:52:34.323 --> 00:52:35.842
Uh. Johnny. can we talk?

1103
00:52:35.980 --> 00:52:38.016
Mm.

1104
00:52:40.398 --> 00:52:42.952
Oh. you always gotta have these
guys around to hear everything?

1105
00:52:43.090 --> 00:52:45.231
- Well. what's there to hear?
- Some things.

1106
00:52:45.369 --> 00:52:46.473
Oh.

1107
00:52:56.380 --> 00:52:58.175
You need somethin'. Kathy?

1108
00:53:01.316 --> 00:53:02.386
You can't have him.

1109
00:53:02.524 --> 00:53:03.904
Who?

1110
00:53:04.042 --> 00:53:05.734
You know exactly
who I'm talkin' about.

1111
00:53:05.872 --> 00:53:07.184
Benny. You can't have him.

1112
00:53:07.322 --> 00:53:08.909
The club can't have him.
He's mine.

1113
00:53:09.047 --> 00:53:10.818
You know. and if he keeps
ridin' motorcycles.

1114
00:53:10.842 --> 00:53:12.085
he's gonna die.

1115
00:53:12.223 --> 00:53:13.407
One way or another.
it'll kill him.

1116
00:53:13.431 --> 00:53:14.708
And you know this is true.

1117
00:53:14.846 --> 00:53:16.572
What am I supposed
to do about it?

1118
00:53:16.710 --> 00:53:20.404
You know I don't run Benny.
just like you don't run Benny.

1119
00:53:20.542 --> 00:53:23.372
There ain't nobody
can tell that kid nothin'.

1120
00:53:23.510 --> 00:53:25.202
He's grown.

1121
00:53:26.375 --> 00:53:28.791
If he wants to ride a bike.
he'll ride a bike.

1122
00:53:28.929 --> 00:53:30.276
Well. not if you tell him.
Johnny.

1123
00:53:30.414 --> 00:53:31.839
Not if you tell him
he's outta the club.

1124
00:53:31.863 --> 00:53:34.487
- Come on.
- No. he's mine. Johnny. Mine.

1125
00:53:34.625 --> 00:53:35.729
I'm his wife. not you.

1126
00:53:35.867 --> 00:53:37.455
Fuck is that supposed to mean?

1127
00:53:37.593 --> 00:53:39.226
Well. I know you love him.
I love him. too.

1128
00:53:39.250 --> 00:53:41.528
That's why you gotta do this.

1129
00:53:41.666 --> 00:53:43.220
[sighs]

1130
00:53:43.841 --> 00:53:45.877
Uh...

1131
00:53:48.155 --> 00:53:49.950
Are you. are you done?

1132
00:53:51.366 --> 00:53:52.470
I don't know. Am I?

1133
00:53:52.608 --> 00:53:53.758
Oh. you got
anything more to say?

1134
00:53:53.782 --> 00:53:54.921
No. I said it.

1135
00:53:55.059 --> 00:53:56.716
All right. then.
you know. y-you are.

1136
00:53:56.854 --> 00:53:58.269
You're...

1137
00:53:58.407 --> 00:53:59.546
You're done.

1138
00:54:01.548 --> 00:54:02.998
[sighs]

1139
00:54:11.593 --> 00:54:13.180
KATHY:
You can't have him!

1140
00:54:21.396 --> 00:54:23.846
MAN [muffled]:
Shut the fuck up!

1141
00:54:23.984 --> 00:54:26.090
WOMAN:
Why don't you try it?

1142
00:54:28.644 --> 00:54:30.163
MAN:
Shut your fuckin' yap!

1143
00:54:30.301 --> 00:54:32.510
I swear to God.
all you do is bitch.

1144
00:54:32.648 --> 00:54:34.478
Yap. yap. yap!

1145
00:54:34.616 --> 00:54:36.656
I oughta shut that fuckin'
mouth of yours for good.

1146
00:54:36.756 --> 00:54:38.181
WOMAN: If you did.
it'd be the first thing

1147
00:54:38.205 --> 00:54:39.804
- you ever finished...
- Quit the racket!

1148
00:54:39.828 --> 00:54:41.068
I'm sick of that mouth on you.

1149
00:54:41.139 --> 00:54:42.555
WOMAN:
...worthless piece of shit!

1150
00:54:42.693 --> 00:54:44.660
Always acting like
you're so fuckin' tough!

1151
00:54:44.798 --> 00:54:46.500
If it wasn't for my bad back.
I'd have beat

1152
00:54:46.524 --> 00:54:48.157
- your ass blue by now!
- Yeah. lemme get my jacket.

1153
00:54:48.181 --> 00:54:49.458
WOMAN:
My back! My back!

1154
00:54:49.596 --> 00:54:50.953
- I said to quit the racket.
- MAN: Come here!

1155
00:54:50.977 --> 00:54:52.437
WOMAN: What a worthless
piece of shit...

1156
00:54:52.461 --> 00:54:53.714
Come here! I'm gonna put
this belt on you!

1157
00:54:53.738 --> 00:54:54.888
WOMAN:
...you turned out to be!

1158
00:54:54.912 --> 00:54:56.154
- No. no. no!
- Take that!

1159
00:54:56.293 --> 00:54:57.546
- I said. quit the racket!
- MAN: Told you!

1160
00:54:57.570 --> 00:54:59.088
- I told you!
- Fuck!

1161
00:54:59.226 --> 00:55:00.331
[man cries out]

1162
00:55:00.469 --> 00:55:02.299
- [groans]
- Told you. huh?

1163
00:55:02.437 --> 00:55:03.990
- I told you. Didn't I?
- WOMAN: No.

1164
00:55:04.128 --> 00:55:05.854
- Quit it! Quit it!
- WOMAN: No!

1165
00:55:05.992 --> 00:55:06.993
- No!
- [man sobbing]

1166
00:55:07.131 --> 00:55:09.513
Hey. come here. Come here.

1167
00:55:09.651 --> 00:55:11.066
- Come on.
- WOMAN: Stop!

1168
00:55:11.204 --> 00:55:12.550
- Stop it!
- [man choking]

1169
00:55:12.688 --> 00:55:15.588
Stop it! You're gonna kill him!

1170
00:55:15.726 --> 00:55:18.798
Stop it! Stop it!

1171
00:55:18.936 --> 00:55:19.832
[groaning]

1172
00:55:19.833 --> 00:55:21.353
[panting]

1173
00:55:21.490 --> 00:55:23.354
I want you outta here!

1174
00:55:23.492 --> 00:55:26.702
Don't you ever come back here!
Don't you ever!

1175
00:55:27.910 --> 00:55:29.843
[panting]

1176
00:55:35.090 --> 00:55:36.367
WOMAN [softly]:
I'm sorry.

1177
00:55:36.505 --> 00:55:38.990
I'm sorry. [sobbing]

1178
00:55:39.128 --> 00:55:40.337
I'm sorry.

1179
00:55:40.475 --> 00:55:41.683
Sorry.

1180
00:55:45.928 --> 00:55:47.516
[breathing heavily]

1181
00:55:50.139 --> 00:55:51.865
KID:
Who's comin'?

1182
00:55:52.003 --> 00:55:55.352
[energetic rock music playing]

1183
00:56:03.843 --> 00:56:05.189
[engine starts]

1184
00:56:14.267 --> 00:56:16.442
- [music stops]
- [indistinct chatter]

1185
00:56:17.684 --> 00:56:18.684
What's the matter?

1186
00:56:18.720 --> 00:56:20.722
[indistinct chatter continues]

1187
00:56:28.005 --> 00:56:29.386
KID:
Hey. hey.

1188
00:56:31.664 --> 00:56:33.424
You a Vandal?

1189
00:56:33.562 --> 00:56:34.598
That's right.

1190
00:56:34.736 --> 00:56:36.016
All right. well.
me and the guys.

1191
00:56:36.082 --> 00:56:38.084
you know.
we're looking to join up.

1192
00:56:38.222 --> 00:56:39.603
- You wanna join...
- Uh-huh.

1193
00:56:39.741 --> 00:56:41.432
...you gotta talk to the man.

1194
00:56:42.260 --> 00:56:43.952
Oh. yeah? Who's the man?

1195
00:56:45.056 --> 00:56:46.886
Who's the man?

1196
00:56:51.718 --> 00:56:53.444
That's the man.

1197
00:56:56.102 --> 00:56:57.448
Come on.

1198
00:56:59.208 --> 00:57:01.763
Hey. look at this guy.

1199
00:57:01.901 --> 00:57:03.396
- BRUCIE: Hey. welcome back.
- JOHNNY: Wow.

1200
00:57:03.420 --> 00:57:05.456
You rode in all the way on that?

1201
00:57:05.594 --> 00:57:06.837
I strapped it to the bike.

1202
00:57:06.975 --> 00:57:08.401
He needs it
'cause his leg is broke.

1203
00:57:08.425 --> 00:57:09.643
- Hey. Betty.
- BETTY: Hey. Kathy.

1204
00:57:09.667 --> 00:57:11.566
I need a drink.

1205
00:57:11.704 --> 00:57:14.085
So. uh. what's it like
ridin' on the old foot?

1206
00:57:14.223 --> 00:57:16.087
[motorcycle approaching]

1207
00:57:20.954 --> 00:57:22.818
[engine revs]

1208
00:57:27.478 --> 00:57:29.169
[engine shuts off]

1209
00:57:32.069 --> 00:57:33.139
Hey. man.

1210
00:57:34.347 --> 00:57:36.349
Somebody told me you're the guy
I need to talk to.

1211
00:57:38.558 --> 00:57:39.732
Maybe.

1212
00:57:39.870 --> 00:57:42.528
Blew out here from California.

1213
00:57:42.666 --> 00:57:45.634
Heard there was a big picnic.
wanted to check it out.

1214
00:57:45.772 --> 00:57:48.016
Heard you're the man in charge.

1215
00:57:48.948 --> 00:57:50.570
I'm Sonny.

1216
00:57:50.708 --> 00:57:52.296
I was hoping maybe to...

1217
00:57:53.228 --> 00:57:55.368
...little food.
little to drink...

1218
00:57:56.300 --> 00:57:58.820
...camp out for a night or two.

1219
00:57:58.958 --> 00:58:01.118
Wanted to show a little class.
contribute to the party.

1220
00:58:02.099 --> 00:58:04.308
All right. Help yourself.

1221
00:58:04.446 --> 00:58:05.689
This here's Brucie.

1222
00:58:05.827 --> 00:58:08.519
This. uh. Benny right there
with the boot.

1223
00:58:08.657 --> 00:58:10.556
And I'm Johnny.

1224
00:58:10.694 --> 00:58:12.143
We're the Vandals.

1225
00:58:12.281 --> 00:58:13.662
SONNY:
Well...

1226
00:58:14.801 --> 00:58:16.700
...it's nice to meet
some proper fuck-ups.

1227
00:58:16.838 --> 00:58:19.081
["I'm Going Home"
by The Sonics playing]

1228
00:58:19.219 --> 00:58:22.257
[men hollering]

1229
00:58:27.296 --> 00:58:28.656
- [grunting]
- ♪ When I was a boy ♪

1230
00:58:28.781 --> 00:58:30.679
♪ I had a mind of my own ♪

1231
00:58:32.405 --> 00:58:34.200
- ♪ Told my folks ♪
- [yelling]

1232
00:58:34.338 --> 00:58:35.788
♪ I was leaving home ♪

1233
00:58:37.306 --> 00:58:38.653
[whooping]

1234
00:58:38.791 --> 00:58:40.896
Vandals. motherfucker!

1235
00:58:42.001 --> 00:58:43.278
BRUCIE:
I always wondered

1236
